Here's the full setup:

**XAML — wrap CollectionView in RefreshView for pull-to-refresh:**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1"
                           Text="{Binding Name}"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <ContentView>
                <Label Text="No items found."
                       HorizontalOptions="Center"
                       VerticalOptions="Center" />
            </ContentView>
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel bindings you need:**

| Property / Command | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Items` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | Data source — use ObservableCollection so UI auto-updates |
| `CurrentItem` | `Item` (TwoWay) | Tracks selected item; reset to `null` after navigating so the user can re-select |
| `IsRefreshing` | `bool` | Bound to RefreshView; set `false` when API call completes |
| `ItemSelectedCommand` | `IAsyncRelayCommand` | Fires on selection — navigate to detail page |
| `RefreshCommand` | `IAsyncRelayCommand` | Fires on pull-down — reload from API |

**ViewModel sketch (MVVM Toolkit):**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            ["Item"] = CurrentItem
        });
        CurrentItem = null; // reset so user can re-select same item
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
            {
                Items.Clear();
                foreach (var item in data)
                    Items.Add(item);
            });
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // MUST set false or spinner hangs
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- **`IsRefreshing = false`** in `finally` — otherwise the refresh spinner never stops.
- **`CurrentItem = null`** after navigation — allows re-selecting the same item.
- **Update collections on the UI thread** via `MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`.
- **Never use `ViewCell`** in the template — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, etc.
- Set **`x:DataType`** on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings and better performance.
